events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Quarterback Jordan Jefferson scored on his first play back from suspension, cornerback Tyrann Mathieu scored after setting an LSU record for career forced fumbles, and the No. 1 Tigers methodically defeated Kentucky 35-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jefferson scores in return; No. 1 LSU cruises

events.name: Ball State Cardinals at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: No. 2 Oklahoma 62, Ball St. 6
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones tosses 5 TDs; Oklahoma trounces Ball St.

events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Trent Richardson ran for 181 yards and two touchdowns, breaking tackles and carrying defenders along the way, and No. 3 Alabama rolled No. 12 Florida 38-10 Saturday night in an early season matchup of Southeastern Conference heavyweights.

events.name: Nevada Wolf Pack at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Doug Martin ran for two touchdowns and Boise State 's suffocating defense shut down Nevada's potent offense to help the No. 4 Broncos cruise to a 30-10 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 Boise State's defense suffocates Nevada

events.name: UCLA Bruins at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: No. 6 Stanford 45, UCLA 19

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: No. 7 Wisconsin 48, No. 8 Nebraska 17

events.name: Auburn Tigers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Barrett Trotter's 9-yard touchdown pass to Phillip Lutzenkirchen with 1:38 left lifted Auburn to a 16-13 victory over No. 10 South Carolina on Saturday.

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd and No. 13 Clemson became the first Atlantic Coast Conference team to beat ranked teams three weeks in a row, and did it resoundingly with a 23-3 victory against No. 11 Virginia Tech on Saturday.

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson and Jarius Wright shattered school records for passing and receiving, and Broderick Green ran 3 yards for the go-ahead touchdown with 1:41 left as No. 18 Arkansas beat No. 14 Texas A&M 42-38 Saturday.

events.name: Baylor Bears at Kansas State Wildcats

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III threw his first interception at exactly the wrong time.
headlines.shortLinkText: K-State picks off Griffin, No. 15 Baylor late

events.name: Texas Longhorns at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Freshman David Ash threw for 145 yards and his first two career touchdown passes and 17th-ranked Texas drilled Iowa State 37-14 in the Big 12 opener for both teams.

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Denard Robinson threw two touchdown passes and ran for a TD to lead No. 19 Michigan in a 58-0 win over Minnesota.

events.name: SMU Mustangs at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: J.J. McDermott threw a 19-yard touchdown pass to Jeremy Johnson in overtime and SMU recovered from a fourth-quarter comeback for a 40-33 upset of No. 20 TCU on Saturday.

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Orwin Smith rushed for three touchdowns and No. 21 Georgia Tech beat North Carolina State 45-35 on Saturday to extend its best start in more than 20 years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith runs unbeaten Ga. Tech past NC State

events.name: Bowling Green Falcons at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Freshman Dustin Garrison rushed for 291 yards and two touchdowns to lead No. 22 West Virginia to a 55-10 win over Bowling Green on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garrison runs for 291 to boost West Virginia

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Quarterback Nathan Scheelhaase scored a 1-yard touchdown with 13 seconds left Saturday to lead No. 24 Illinois to a 38-35 comeback win over Northwestern.

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: No. 25 Arizona St. 35, Oregon St. 20
headlines.shortLinkText: Arizona St. survives mistakes, beats Oregon St.

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description:
Aaron Murray threw two touchdown passes in
the first quarter, Isaiah Crowell ran for 104 yards and Georgia 
took advantage of a strong start to beat Mississippi State 24-10 on
 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia tops Miss. St. despite 2nd-half malaise

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Matt McGloin threw a 74-yard touchdown pass to Derek Moye late in the third quarter, leading Penn State to a 16-10 victory Saturday at Indiana.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn St. clips Indiana to win Big Ten opener

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: San San Te kicked a 47-yard field goal in the second overtime and seconds later the Rutgers defense recovered a fumble by Syracuse's Antwon Bailey, giving the Scarlet Knights a 19-16 victory in the Big East opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rutgers converts long kick to outlast Syracuse

events.name: Toledo Rockets at Temple Owls

headlines.description: David Fluellen scored two touchdowns to help Toledo score 21 unanswered points and beat Temple 36-13 on Saturday in the Mid-American Conference opener for both teams.

events.name: Tulane Green Wave at Army Black Knights

headlines.description: Quarterback Trent Steelman threw for 70 yards and a touchdown and ran for two more touchdowns as Army routed Tulane 45-6 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Steelman accounts for 3 TDs; Army rolls Tulane

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description:
Seth Doege passed for 366 yards and three 
touchdowns and Eric Stephens rushed for 112 yards and scored twice, helping Texas Tech come roaring back from a 20-point deficit and 
beat Kansas 45-34 Saturday in both teams' Big 12 opener.

events.name: Air Force Falcons at Navy Midshipmen

headlines.description: Tim Jefferson ran for a 1-yard touchdown in overtime and Parker Herrington added the conversion to give Air Force a wild 35-34 victory over Navy on Saturday, a significant first step in the Falcons' bid to retain the coveted Commander-in-Chief's Trophy.
headlines.shortLinkText: Air Force hangs on to win after Navy forces OT

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Tanner Price threw a 47-yard TD pass to Chris Givens on Wake Forest's first possession of the second half as the Demon Deacons opened a 15-point lead before holding off Boston College 27-19 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wake rides Price's arm, thwarts Boston College

events.name: Buffalo Bulls at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Tyler Bray threw four touchdowns, Da'Rick Rogers caught two of them and DeAnthony Arnett caught two more as Tennessee beat Buffalo 41-10 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bray, Rogers help Tennessee stomp Buffalo

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Miami (OH) RedHawks

headlines.description: Isaiah Pead ran for a pair of touchdowns Saturday, and Cincinnati's dominating defense opened the second half with a goal-line stand that set up a 27-0 victory over Miami of Ohio.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pead runs for 2 TDs as Cincy rolls Miami (Ohio)

headlines.description: Wofford 28, Appalachian St. 14

events.name: Arizona Wildcats at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Matt Barkley passed for a school-record 468 yards and four touchdowns, Robert Woods made 14 catches for 255 yards and two scores, and Southern California outlasted Arizona 48-41 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barkley sets record as USC takes down Arizona

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Marquess Wilson sped past two defenders and hauled in a 63-yard touchdown pass from Marshall Lobbestael with 1:10 left to lead Washington State to a stunning 31-27 comeback win over Colorado on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wazzu's late TD spoils Colorado's Pac-12 debut

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Alex Carder threw for a career-high 479 yards and five touchdowns to lead Western Michigan to a 38-31 win over Connecticut on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: W. Michigan throws for 479 yards to stun UConn

events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at Louisville Cardinals

headlines.description: Rakeem Cato's 4-yard touchdown pass to C.J. Crawford put Marshall ahead with less than two minutes left in the fourth quarter and the Thundering Herd held on to beat Louisville 17-13 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Crawford's late TD lifts Marshall over Louisville

events.name: Towson Tigers at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Danny O'Brien threw two second half touchdowns and Maryland's defense forced four second half turnovers, helping the Terrapins pull away to a 28-3 win over in-state foes Towson on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Terrapins pull away from Towson in second half

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins threw a 33-yard scoring pass to B.J. Cunningham and Michigan State's No. 1-ranked defense overwhelmed Ohio State 10-7 Saturday, shutting out the Buckeyes until the final seconds.

events.name: Washington Huskies at Utah Utes

headlines.description: Keith Price threw three touchdown passes, Chris Polk rushed for 189 yards to surpass 3,000 in his career and Washington cruised to a 31-14 victory over Utah on Saturday, spoiling the Utes' first Pac-12 home game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington rolls in Utah's Pac-12 home opener
